Bug Hunter: You are reviewing the following code snippet designed to deduplicate JPA entities in a transactional service. Even though a `HashSet` is used, duplicates of the same `Product` entity (with the same ID) are appearing in the resulting `Set` after several database updates.

java
@Service
public class InventoryManager {
    private final Set<Product> uniqueProducts = new HashSet<>();

    @Transactional
    public void processUpdate(Long productId) {
        Product product = repository.getById(productId); 
        // Product entity uses @GeneratedValue ID and standard field-based equals/hashCode
        uniqueProducts.add(product);
    }
}
